About
============================
This is a  GSOC 2012 project, the objective is write a tool 
to visualize Bluetooth traffic as sequence diagrams.

Developed by:
Student Thiago da Silva Arruda <thiago.xth1@gmail.com>
Mentor Gustavo Padovan <gustavo@padovan.org> 

Compilation and installation
============================

In order to compile Bluetooth utilities you need following software packages:
	- Linux Bluetooth protocol stack (BlueZ)
	- GCC compiler
	- D-Bus library
	- GLib library
	- GTK+ libary
	- Cairo libary

To genenerate configure script:
	./bootstrap
	./bootstrap-configure

To configure run:
	./configure --prefix=/usr --mandir=/usr/share/man \
		--sysconfdir=/etc --localstatedir=/var --libexecdir=/lib

Configure automatically searches for all required components and packages.

To compile and install run:
	make && make install


